data.description: When Bruce Kilgore designed his first basketball shoe for Nike, he had no idea it would be reinvented innumerable times over the coming decades. The Nike Women’s Air Force 1 '07 Mid ‘Tokyo 2003' is a lavish celebration of this iconic court shoe, with a vivid violet Swoosh, tongue tag and ankle strap. Violet faux-croc embossed overlays in Viotech pop against a Summit White leather upper. The rubber cupsole underfoot is boosted by Nike Air cushioning. A salute to Tokyo culture is delivered with the embossed 'TYO 03' on the outside heel.

Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Crimson Bliss
data.description: The DJ Khaled x Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Crimson Bliss’ sees a classic silhouette through a new lens, in his ‘We the Best’ collection. The upper in a vibrant coral leather is contrasted with a silky quilted lining in Leche Blue, with the heel overlays adorned with a blue embroidered Nike Air logo on the right and 'We the Best' on the left. The silver reflective tongue features the classic Jumpman branding, and the translucent rubber outsoles complete the playful logo treatment with additional Jumpman and ‘We the Best’ branding. Underfoot, an off-white polyurethane midsole with blue speckled shark-tooth detailing is complemented by a visible Air-sole unit in the heel.

data.shoeName: Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Sail
data.description: The DJ Khaled x Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Sail' uses pastel hues and subtle logo highlights for its part in the ‘We the Best’ capsule collection. An off-white leather upper is highlighted by pastel embellishments and a powder-blue quilted lining, contrasting with the Air-assisted polyurethane midsole in Violet Star. The tongue features the classic Jumpman logo against a reflective silver finish, with 'Keep Going' hidden on its interior side. The two heel overlays contrast, with one adorned by the Nike Air log while the other proclaiming 'We the Best,' which also decorates the right shoe's translucent rubber outsole.

data.shoeName: Jordan 5 Retro Grape (2013)
data.description: The 2013 edition of the Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Grape’ brings back one of the silhouette’s OG colorways from 1990. The reissue features a design that’s mostly true to the original, though Jumpman branding replaces the traditional Nike Air heel embroidery. The shoe’s unique purple and teal accents are complemented by signature Jordan 5 details, including lace locks and a translucent rubber outsole.

data.shoeName: Jordan 3 Retro Crimson (GS)
data.description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro GS ‘Crimson’ gives the retro silhouette a minimalist design that stays true to classic Jordan heritage. A black leather upper is accented by pops of Bright Crimson on the eyelets, collar lining and midsole. The shoe’s signature elephant-print overlays, placed in their traditional locations, are tinted in purple, with the same hue reappearing on the rubber outsole.

data.description: The Nike Air Max Penny 1 ‘All-Star’ brings back Penny Hardaway’s first signature shoes, first seen at the 1996 NBA All-Star Game. The black upper in nubuck features a metallic silver Swoosh accented by piping in royal blue; additional Swooshes embellish the toe box and tongue. The heel is adorned with a stitched 1Cent logo. Comfort on and off the court is ensured by a Phylon midsole in black with a Max Air unit in the heel.

New Balance 9060 Truffle Rich Earth Magnet

Nike Air Zoom Flight 95 Black Valerian Blue
data.description: Honoring the origins of Zoom Air techology is the Nike Air Zoom Flight 95 ‘Black Valerian Blue.’ In this pair, a Zoom Air unit appears on the forefoot with an Air-sole unit in the heel within a chunky Phylon midsole. Familiar ‘bug eyes’ adorn the sidewall. Black nubuck infuses the upper, complemented by Ale Brown piping, tonal stitching and an overlay in tumbled leather. The toe box features branding with an oversized Swoosh and a lateral-side Swoosh outlined in blue.

data.shoeName: New Balance 2002R Up There Backyard Legends II
Nike Air Humara LX Jacquemus Pink Flash (W)
data.description: Nike and Jacquemus collaborate for a third time with the Jacquemus x Nike Women’s Air Humara LX ‘Pink Flash.’ With the 1997 Humara as its inspiration, this pair features a mesh upper in a vibrant pink hue combined with fuzzy suede color-matched overlays embellished with a gilded Swoosh. The stitched-leather lace tips deliver additional Nike branding while the back heel and tongue tag salute Jacquemus. The midsole is bolstered by a wrapping in pink textile and Air-sole cushioning while a gum rubber outsole delivers comfort and grip.
